theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_open
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    exact closure_mono
      (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A)
  · -- `⊇` direction
    -- Since `A` is open, it sits inside `interior (closure A)`.
    have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) hA
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    exact closure_mono hSub

nonrec theorem interior_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) ⊆
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Since `interior A ⊆ A`, taking closures preserves the inclusion.
  have h : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
  -- Applying monotonicity of `interior` finishes the proof.
  exact interior_mono h

theorem P3_implies_closure_eq_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) →
      closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP3
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    have h : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
    exact (closure_mono h)
  · -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
    have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact (closure_mono h)

theorem interior_union_satisfies_all_Ps
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A B : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (interior A ∪ interior B) ∧
      Topology.P2 (interior A ∪ interior B) ∧
      Topology.P3 (interior A ∪ interior B) := by
  -- The interiors of any sets are open.
  have hOpenA : IsOpen (interior A) := isOpen_interior
  have hOpenB : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
  -- Apply the existing lemma for unions of open sets.
  simpa using
    (Topology.open_union_satisfies_all_Ps
      (A := interior A) (B := interior B) hOpenA hOpenB)
